# 6. 距離

Airi: (*Sigh* I don't have work today. That means I can have lunch at school for a change...)
Airi: It'd be nice to eat with someone...
Airi: Shizuku...isn't here. Pretty sure she has that magazine shoot today.
Airi: Hmm... Who else is there...?
Airi: Oh, of course...!
Airi: Let's see... Class A should be...
???: Huh? Airi?
Airi: Ayumi, perfect! I was just looking for you! Wanna have lunch together today?
Ayumi: Wait, really?
Airi: Yes, really. I just happen to not have work today.
Ayumi: Wow, this is great! We haven't been able to hang out at all since we entered high school and you switched courses...
Ayumi: Oh, is it okay if I invite a few others? Remember the classmates I introduced you to the other day? We always eat together.
Airi: Yeah, of course! They're welcome to join if they want.
Ayumi: Okay, I'll go ask them now. Airi, you wait for us down in the courtyard!
Student A: You and Momoi went to the same junior high, Ayumi? When did you two become friends?
Airi: During our first year. Our seats were next to each other and we just hit it off.
Ayumi: Yeah, we really did!
Student A: Wow. You must've been surprised when you saw a famous idol who's on TV all the time sitting next to you.
Ayumi: Actually, no. That was before she debuted as an idol.
Student B: Really? Can you tell us what you were like back then?
Airi: Not all that different from now. I was already in love with idols then...
Airi: Oh, but I was pretty rowdy when I was a kid. I preferred to play outside and even got into fights with some boys...
Airi: I put all that behind me when I decided to become an idol. Instead, I began learning more about fashion and started working on my singing and dancing.
Student A: And your dream actually came true? That's so cool, Momoi!
Airi: I dunno. It feels more like I've been given a chance to make it happen as opposed to it actually coming true.
Airi: Oh, while we're on the subject... Ayumi helped me out a bunch when I was still trying to become an idol.
Ayumi: Wait, me? What did I do?
Airi: Hehe. I suppose it didn't seem like much from your perspective...
Airi: But you never put down my dream of becoming an idol. You always supported me.
Junior High School Ayumi: What? You want to become an idol...?
Junior High School Ayumi: Wow... Th-That's amazing...! I'm sure you can, Airi! No, I know you can...!
Airi: What you said that time made me so happy. Most people tended to laugh or snicker when I told them how I wanted to become an idol.
Airi: So, it was nice to hear someone giving me their support. You gave me so much encouragement.
Student A: Wow, that really happened? Way to go, Ayumi!
Ayumi: I-It meant that much to you...?
Ayumi: But I was just telling you how I felt...
Airi: Huh?
Ayumi: I mean, Airi, you've always had this brilliant aura about you.
Ayumi: On the day of the entrance ceremony, none of my friends were in my class and I had a lot of trouble talking to anyone else...
Ayumi: Everyone around was chatting and sounded like they were having so much fun... Without me... That made me feel so anxious...
Ayumi: Airi then noticed that I looked really concerned...
Ayumi: She was actually talking to someone else, but went out of her way to greet me.
Ayumi: She said, “Hi, I'm Airi Momoi. Nice to meet you.”
Ayumi: It was a really simple greeting, but it made me feel so much better for some reason...
Ayumi: After that, we kept talking and eventually became really close...
Airi: Yeah, I remember that now...
Ayumi: I won't ever forget. I mean, when you first spoke to me that day, you were enveloped in this incredible aura...
Airi: Ayumi...
Ayumi: It's why I thought it was totally possible when you told me that you wanted to become an idol. If anything, I believed you were really cut out for it.
Airi: You did...? It's a little embarrassing to hear that so directly... But thanks. I really appreciate it.
Student A: The Momoi in that story is exactly what we're used to seeing on TV!
Student B: You really are a friendly and caring person. I wish I was that close with you.
Airi: Hehe. Thanks! I'd like that as well.
Airi: I know. Why don't you all take this opportunity to start calling me by my first name? That should make things easier, right?
Student A: Really?! Then...! I hope we get to hang out more, Airi!
Airi: Yeah, me too!
Airi: Okay, I have the meeting for that variety show tomorrow afternoon.
Airi: (I'm still not sure how I feel about appearing on one of these shows, but I have a duty to fulfill.)
Airi: I also have that test coming up. I'll need to make some time to study for it. But when...?
Airi: Oh, a message from Ayumi?
Airi: (Maybe she wants to have lunch. Come to think of it, I haven't been able to join them lately because work has been so busy...)
Airi: (And yet, she's still inviting me... I couldn't be more grateful.)
Ayumi's Message: <Airi, have you heard about the field trip already?>
Airi: Field trip?
Ayumi's Message: <Apparently, we're going to PXL and are gonna have some free time to ourselves.>
Ayumi's Message: <We can go around the park with people from other classes during that time. Wanna hang out?>
Airi: Right, the field trip... It's really soon, but I'm pretty sure that I...
Airi: Yeah, I have a shoot that day.
Airi: <As fun as that sounds, I'm really sorry. I have a shoot that day and can't go...>
Airi: ...
Airi: (She's taking a while to reply...)
Ayumi's Message: <That's okay! I know you're really busy. We can always hang out another time!>
Airi: <Yeah, let's do that one of these days.>
Airi: One of these days...
Airi: (Is that day ever going to come...?)
Airi: *Sigh* That shoot went quicker than I expected. If I head home now, I'll have some time to study.
Airi: (Oh, wait... Wasn't everyone supposed to go on that field trip today?)
Airi: (I hope Ayumi and the others had fun... I'll send her a message later when...)
Ayumi: Hehe. That was so much fun. We should go again together sometime.
Airi: (Huh? That sounded like...)
Airi: Ayumi!
Ayumi: Huh? Airi?
Ayumi: What are you doing here? I thought you were working...
Airi: It ended sooner than expected, so I'm on my way home now. Are you guys just coming back?
Ayumi: Yeah! PXL was really fun!
Student A: It'd been a while since I last went, but it was even more fun than I remembered. I sort of couldn't help but go all out.
Student B: Oh, hang on. We took a bunch of pictures, Airi. Wanna see?
Airi: Yeah, lemme see!
Student B: Where do we start? Oh, how about this one? It's the one of us just after we came out of the haunted house...
Student A: Oh, yeah... You were totally terrified, Ayumi. Remember when you screamed your lungs out and shoved us forward? You almost made us fall over.
Ayumi: H-Hey, no one else needs to know about that. Let's look at a different one...
Student B: Hehe. What else was there? Hmm... Oh, here's when we went to watch that show...
Ayumi: Hey, this is the one we got to take with Phenny! He was so cute!
Student A: He really was! I took a bunch with him too!
Airi: Hehe. Looks like you all had a lot of fun.
Ayumi: We did! Oh, how amazing was that show?
Student B: Yeah, the one at the Phoenix Stage? They definitely weren't some run-of-the-mill troupe.
Student A: The churros we got after were also really good. They even had some that were melon soda flavored. I wish I could've given that a try.
Ayumi: Hehe. We can get some the next time we go!
Ayumi: That includes you, Airi!
Airi: Huh? R-Right...! Next time, we...
Airi: One of these days...
Airi: (Is that day ever going to come...?)
Airi: ...
Airi: (If I raise their hopes again, only to dash them in the end...)
Ayumi: Um, Airi?
Airi: Huh? Oh, sorry. I spaced out there for a second.
Airi: So, PXL... Yeah, next time... Let's go together.
Ayumi: Oh...
Ayumi: ...
Ayumi: Airi... I'm sorry. I was so thoughtless...
Airi: Huh?
Ayumi: I knew you were busy with work and all, but I kept sending you messages and inviting you to hang out...
Airi: What...? N-No, don't worry about that. I really appreciate how you've been inviting me out and stuff!
Ayumi: Okay, thanks. I appreciate you being so polite about this, Airi.
Airi: No, I really do...
Ayumi: Oh, I almost forgot...! I took some pictures too! Wanna see?
Ayumi: The view from the Ferris wheel was so pretty. I hope those turned out okay...
Airi: Oh...
Student B: Whoa, hey, this one! I have such a stupid look on my face... When did you take this?!
Ayumi: Oh... Hehe. I couldn't help it. It was just too funny...
Student B: Really? That's your excuse... Delete it right now...!
Student A: What?! No, wait! I wanna see! You're not allowed to delete it until I do!
Airi: (I was just...)
Airi: (It's not a bother... Really...)
Airi: (But...)
Student B: Gimme your phone, Ayumi! I'm getting rid of that pic before anyone else has a chance to see it!
Ayumi: Hey, wait! Gimme back my phone!
Airi: (I guess there's nothing I can do about this...)
Airi: (I placed work before hanging out with my friends. And Ayumi said what she did just now because...)
Airi: (This is the path I chose...)
Airi: (Still...)
Ayumi: Oh, this is the last one we took together! It turned out a lot better than I realized!
Airi: (I didn't realize it'd feel this lonely not being included...)
